iguration for /mem/ is incorrect.
Let's check the nginx proxy configuration:
bash# Check the current nginx mem proxy config
grep -A 10 "location /mem/" /etc/nginx/sites-available/api.nsgia.com

# The issue might be the proxy_pass URL
# Current config should show: proxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/mem/;
# But it might need to be: proxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/;
Let's fix the nginx configuration:
bashsudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/api.nsgia.com
Change the /mem/ location block from:
nginxproxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/mem/;
To:
nginxproxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/;
Then reload nginx and test:
bashsudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx

# Test the fixed endpoint
curl -I "https://api.nsgia.com/mem/get?id=1369de11-d01f-4cb5-9b37-87d26ef0677b&key=public-read-2025"
This should fix the proxy path and make all four endpoints work! ðŸŽ¯
What does the current nginx config show for the /mem/ block?RetryMHCheck the current nginx mem proxy config
grep -A 10 "location /mem/" /etc/nginx/sites-available/api.nsgia.com
# The issue might be the proxy_pass URL
# Current config should show: proxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/mem/;
# But it might need to be: proxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/;
    location /mem/ {
        proxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/mem/;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto https;
        proxy_buffering off;
        proxy_redirect off;        # Keep HTML content type from backend
        add_header Access-Control-Allow-Origin "*" always;
        add_header Access-Control-Allow-Methods "GET, OPTIONS" always;
mh@NSG:/var/www/memory_system$EditPerfect! I found the issue. The nginx configuration is exactly as I suspected:
Current (problematic): proxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/mem/;
Should be: proxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/;
The issue is that nginx is sending /mem/get to /mem/mem/
